.LogManager()`, which the dedicated test already exercises. The two remaining call sites are inside a legacy JDK-internal compatibility hack that only proceeds if `java.util.logging.Level$KnownLevel` has the old internal shape expected by JBoss LogManager 1.5.3:\\n\\n- accessible `KnownLevel(java.util.logging.Level)` constructor via `getConstructor(...)`\\n- static fields named `nameToLevels`\\n- static fields named `intToLevels`\\n\\nOn the supported/current JDK used by this repository, that internal JDK class no longer has the expected accessible constructor/fields, so `LogManager` catches the failure and intentionally skips the `KnownLevelBuilder` path before either `Constructor#newInstance(...)` call can execute.\\n\\nBecause `KnownLevelBuilder` is private and only reachable through this obsolete JDK-internal branch, reaching the two remaining call sites would require directly reflecting into private library internals or shadowing/patching `java.util.logging.Level$KnownLevel`, both of which are disallowed by the task rules.\\n\\nI left the dedicated public-API test in place:\\n\\n- `tests/src/org.jboss.logmanager/jboss-logmanager/1.5.3.Final/src/test/java/org_jboss_logmanager/jboss_logmanager/LogManagerInnerKnownLevelBuilderTest.java`\\n\\nIt exercises the supported constructor path and verifies the public JUL level parsing behavior, but the two legacy `KnownLevelBuilder.add(...)` call sites remain unreachable on the current supported JDK without violating the constraints.\", \"textSignature\": \"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_061ae871c3261499016a23839ca8ac8194863679ddf023648b\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"oca/gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 40656, \"output\": 858, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 41514, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"stop\", \"timestamp\": 1780712334798, \"responseId\": \"resp_061ae871c3261499016a23838fb2e48194ba68ae8bb9c6f00b\"}, \"toolResults\": []}\n2713:[recv] get_state success\n2717:[recv] get_session_stats success\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
