{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_31","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `org.jboss.logmanager:jboss-logmanager:1.5.3.Final`. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-7920-fails-java-run-org.jboss.logmanager-jboss-logmanager-1.5.3.Final-7f778302\n\nThe first concrete failure was in the Java `:test` stage: `FormattersAnonymous12Anonymous2Test` failed with `ClassNotFoundException: org.jboss.logmanager.formatters.Formatters$11$3`, which points to the copied 1.4.1.Final test still targeting stale anonymous-class numbering in 1.5.3.Final. See `human-intervention-logs/org.jboss.logmanager:jboss-logmanager:1.5.3.Final/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-06T02-04-06-402648Z.log` and `human-intervention-logs/org.jboss.logmanager:jboss-logmanager:1.5.3.Final/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-06-06T02-07-50-587939Z.log`.\n\nAfter that was addressed, native verification exposed missing shipped metadata for `org.jboss.logmanager.AtomicArray#add(java.lang.Object, java.lang.Object)` in `human-intervention-logs/org.jboss.logmanager:jboss-logmanager:1.5.3.Final/native-test-verify/cycle-1-runNativeTraceImage-2026-06-06T02-08-41-790323Z.log`. The preserved branch does appear to contain a viable candidate: later focused reruns in `human-intervention-logs/org.jboss.logmanager:jboss-logmanager:1.5.3.Final/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-06T02-19-14-203493Z.log` and `human-intervention-logs/org.jboss.logmanager:jboss-logmanager:1.5.3.Final/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-06T02-20-29-821103Z.log` end with `BUILD SUCCESSFUL`, and `stats/org.jboss.logmanager/jboss-logmanager/1.5.3.Final/execution-metrics.json` reports `status: success`. However, `stats/org.jboss.logmanager/jboss-logmanager/1.5.3.Final/stats.json` still shows dynamic-access coverage at `32/34` (`94.12%`), and the second coverage pass concludes the 2 remaining reflective calls in `LogManager$KnownLevelBuilder.add(...)` are behind obsolete `java.util.logging.Level$KnownLevel` internals and are not reachable through supported public API on the current JDK; see `human-intervention-logs/org.jboss.logmanager:jboss-logmanager:1.5.3.Final/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-06-06T02-15-52-281378Z.log`.\n\nNext steps:\n1. Review the preserved branch diff, especially the renamed formatter test, the new `LogManagerInnerKnownLevelBuilderTest`, and `metadata/org.jboss.logmanager/jboss-logmanager/1.5.3.Final/reachability-metadata.json`.\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.jboss.logmanager:jboss-logmanager:1.5.3.Final` (and `checkMetadataFiles` if needed) from the preserved branch to confirm the candidate is still green.\n3. Decide whether the remaining 2 `KnownLevelBuilder` reflective calls should be accepted as unreachable on supported JDKs or need a maintainer-authored follow-up before merging."}}
